<h3><a id="user-content-appenddata" class="deep-link" href="#appenddata" aria-hidden="true" rel="nofollow"><svg aria-hidden="true" class="deep-link-icon" height="16" version="1.1" viewbox="0 0 16 16" width="16"><path d="M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"></path></svg></a><code>appendData</code></h3>
<p>Type: <code>String|Function</code>
Default: <code>undefined</code></p>
<p>AppendData <code>Less</code> code after the actual entry file.</p>
<p>This can be useful when you need to rewrite some of your Less variables.:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>ℹ Since you're injecting code, this will break the source mappings in your entry file. Often there's a simpler solution than this, like multiple Less entry files.</p>
</blockquote>
